{"id":"scaffold-2wg","title":"fix(tests): pre-push hook breaks setup-agent-worktree tests when run from worktree context","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen `git push` is run from inside a worktree (e.g., `.worktrees/remove-ci-gate/`), the pre-push hook runs the full test suite. Git sets `GIT_DIR` to the current .git path in hook environments, which causes `git clone` calls inside `tests/setup-agent-worktree.bats` setup to fail:\n\n```\nfatal: repository '/private/var/.../T/orig-XXXXX' does not exist\n```\n\nTests 42-46 (setup-agent-worktree.bats) all fail with this error.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn `tests/test_helper/common-setup.bash` (or the bats setup function), `git clone \"$ORIG_DIR\" \"$CLONE_DIR\"` is called. When `GIT_DIR` is set in the environment (as git does for hooks), git ignores `$ORIG_DIR` and tries to use `GIT_DIR` instead — pointing at a non-existent temp path.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn the pre-push hook script (or a hook wrapper), unset the git environment variables that interfere with subprocess git operations:\n```bash\nunset GIT_DIR GIT_WORK_TREE GIT_INDEX_FILE\n```\nThis should be done before invoking `make test`.\n\nAlternatively, fix the test setup to explicitly pass `--no-local` or use `GIT_DIR= git clone ...` to reset the variable inline.\n\n## Files\n\n- Hook script that runs tests (check `scripts/` or `.git/hooks/pre-push`)\n- `tests/setup-agent-worktree.bats` (test file with the failing setup)\n- `tests/test_helper/common-setup.bash` (shared test setup)\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n**Category**: manual verification\nAfter fix, run `git push` from within a worktree — tests 42-46 must pass.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Ken Allred","owner":"zigrivers@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-18T15:05:05.92196-07:00","created_by":"Ken Allred","updated_at":"2026-02-18T15:36:02.10643-07:00","closed_at":"2026-02-18T15:36:02.10643-07:00","close_reason":"Closed"}
